🚀 PolyDropBox
Decentralized File Sharing with Expiry, Payments & Cross-Chain Swaps
🔥 BIG PICTURE (What PolyDropBox Is)

PolyDropBox is a WeTransfer + Dropbox + Crypto Payments + Cross-Chain Swap platform where:

Files are stored decentralized (IPFS/Pinata)

Access is controlled by Polygon smart contracts

Payments can be made from ANY chain using SideShift

Files can expire, burn after download, or be NFT-gated

👉 Sender gets paid
👉 Receiver doesn’t need to worry about which chain/token they have
👉 Everything is trustless

🧠 CORE IDEA (1-Minute Understanding)

Creator uploads a file

File is encrypted + stored on IPFS

Creator sets rules (expiry, price, downloads)

A share link is created

Receiver opens link

Receiver pays in ANY crypto via SideShift

SideShift swaps → sends funds to Polygon

Polygon smart contract unlocks file

File is downloaded (or burned)

👤 USER POV (Receiver / Downloader)
🔹 Step 1: Open Share Link

User opens:

https://polydropbox.io/file/xyz


They see:

File name & size

Expiry time

Price (e.g. 2 USDC on Polygon)

Accepted payments:
👉 “Pay with ANY crypto (BTC, ETH, SOL, BNB…)”

🔹 Step 2: Choose Payment Method

User chooses:

✅ Pay directly on Polygon (if they have MATIC/USDC)

🔁 Pay via SideShift (cross-chain)

🔹 Step 3: SideShift Swap Flow (Very Important)

If user clicks “Pay with Any Crypto”:

Your frontend calls SideShift API:

Input asset: user chooses (BTC / ETH / SOL / etc.)

Output asset: USDC (Polygon)

Output address: PolyDropBox smart contract

SideShift returns:

Deposit address (for BTC/ETH/etc.)

Exact amount to send

Time window

User sends crypto to SideShift address

SideShift swaps & sends USDC to Polygon contract

🔹 Step 4: Smart Contract Confirms Payment

Polygon smart contract:

Confirms USDC received

Marks file as paid

Updates download count

Emits AccessGranted event

🔹 Step 5: Secure Download

Backend checks contract state

Decryption key released one time

File downloaded from IPFS

If “burn after download” → access revoked forever

🔹 Step 6: Proof & Receipt

User sees:

Polygon transaction hash

Payment receipt

Download timestamp

